claim.claim-text:
10. A method, comprising:
determining, in a server computing device, a first number of beats per minute based upon an average of a plurality of numbers of beats per minute associated with a plurality of media items previously consumed by a client device;
identifying a plurality of media item candidates from the plurality of media items, wherein respective ones of a plurality of second numbers of beats per minute are associated with individual ones of the plurality of media item candidates;
identifying a subset of the media item candidates based at least upon an association between the first and second numbers of beats per minute; and
sending, in the server computing device, the subset of the media item candidates to the client device.

13. A non-transitory computer-readable medium embodying a program executable in at least one computing device, comprising:
code that determines a first beats per minute value based upon user activity by at least determining an average of a plurality of numbers of beats per minute associated with a selection of consumed media items previously consumed by a client device;
code that identifies a plurality of media item candidates from a plurality of media items, where individual ones of a plurality of second beats per minute values are associated with corresponding ones of the media item candidates, and where the plurality of second beats per minute values are within a predefined delta of the first beats per minute value;
code that filters out predefined ones of the media item candidates that are possessed by a user; and
code that identifies a subset of the media item candidates to surface to the user in at least one recommendation based at least upon information associated with the user.
